race.comment: JUKEBOX LUCY (7) was heavily backed and justified the support when resuming last start over 1050m at Blackall, scoring by a nose. Has a solid second-up record and rates to get the money again. VONK (5) was on a winning run before the 1.6L defeat here heavily bet. Began awkwardly in that and the longer sprint suits. Maps for the run of the race. HEAVENLY LEGEND (6) started at $3.70 last time on the back of a win at this track but didn't have the best of it, well beaten. Draws inside and has a handy 2kg claim. He's capable of bouncing. MANIC LIGHT (8) narrowly missed last time over 1400m at Tara when he was always up in the leading division. Ran a good number and can't be ruled out back to a shorter sprint off a freshen.
